[Course_Description]
Great product photography is essential for any online business. Whether you want to take photographs for your own store or start a new sideline, shoot with a smartphone, mirrorless camera, or high-powered DSLR, you'll benefit from these expert product photography tips. PhotoJoseph Linaschke covers the gear, lighting, and post-processing essentials you need to shoot products of all kinds. First, discover how to get the most out of the photo accessories you already own, work with a white seamless background, and incorporate props. Then learn about lighting, from small flashes to large strobes, and using reflectors and diffusers. Finally, get some tips to make your products look their best with photo editing software like Lightroom and Photoshop. Need a refresher on the basics? Check out Joseph's Photography 101 series.